resource.valueString: Patient's ophthalmology notes will be documented here.
The diagnostic study conducted on the patient's eyes showed no signs of abnormalities. Visual acuity and intraocular pressure were within normal ranges. Further follow-up scheduled in 6 months.

Patient presented with complaints of mild throat pain and occasional hoarseness. Upon examination, the oropharynx appeared inflamed, and a small polyp was observed in the nasal cavity. No signs of infection were noted. Advised the patient to rest the voice and prescribed a short course of anti-inflammatory medication. Reevaluation scheduled in 2 weeks.

The EEG study showed normal brain wave patterns with no signs of seizure activity. No abnormalities were observed during the recording period. Additional neurological evaluation recommended if symptoms persist.
The EKG study showed a normal sinus rhythm with no signs of arrhythmias or abnormalities. The heart rate and intervals were within normal ranges. No immediate concerns identified.
